article.description: Stefan Jankovic scored 22 points on 8-of-11 shooting and grabbed eight rebounds to help Hawaii win its eighth straight on Saturday night, 78-62 over UC Davis.
article.headline: Hawaii beats UC Davis 78-62 for eighth straight win
article.linkText: Hawaii beats UC Davis 78-62 for eighth straight win
article.story: HONOLULU -- Stefan Jankovic scored 22 points on 8-of-11 shooting and grabbed eight rebounds to help Hawaii win its eighth straight on Saturday night, 78-62 over UC Davis. Quincy Smith added 18 points, Isaac Fleming scored 13 and the Rainbow Warriors (16-2, 5-0 Big West Conference) tied UC Irvine atop the conference standings. Hawaii went on an 8-0 run to lead 49-41 on Isaac Fleming's jumper at 14:12 and stretched it to 66-53 with 7:11 left. UC Davis (7-11, 2-3) never got back within single digits. Josh Fox had 25 points and eight rebounds and Brynton Lemar added 12 points. The Aggies trailed 37-35 after closing the first half with eight straight points and tied it with the first basket of the second half. The Aggies tied again at 39 and 41 but never pulled in front.
